-- Absolute, Kumba Iron Ore and Vodacom May Move: South Africa Stocks Preview
-- Nicky Smith
-- 2010-07-22T05:44:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/absolute-kumba-iron-ore-and-vodacom-may-move-south-africa-stocks-preview.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  
 South Africaâ€™s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  gained for a
second time in three days, advancing 483.91, or 1.8 percent, to
27,833.52 at the close in Johannesburg.  
 Absolute Holdings Ltd.  (ABO SJ): The South African mining
company completed a 24.8 million rand ($3.3 million) capital
raising and will issue about 8 million shares at 3.10 rand. The
stock was unchanged at 2.80 rand.  
 Kumba Iron Ore Ltd.  (KIO SJ): The iron ore producer that is
owned by Anglo American Plc said first-half earnings excluding
one-time items jumped 90 percent to 6.49 billion rand ($859
million). Kumba shares added 14.60 rand, or 4.2 percent, to
362.50 rand.  
 Vodacom Group Ltd.  (VOD SJ): The largest provider of mobile
phone services to South Africans said its number of customers
fell 8.7 percent to 37.7 million in the first quarter from a
year earlier. The stock rose 1.40 rand, or 2.3 percent, to 62.80
rand.  
 Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  
 Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) fell 1.3 percent to $18.04.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) slid 0.6 percent to $39.29. BHP
Billiton Plc (BBL US) declined 0.8 percent to $57.48. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) fell 0.7 percent to $4.07. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI
US) lost 0.9 percent to $12.60. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY US)
dropped 1.6 percent to $9.78. Impala Platinum Holdings (IMPUY
US) advanced 0.9 percent to $24.78. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US) lost 0.5
percent to $4.36. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) rose 1.5 percent to
$37.64.  
